      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "Outgoing longwave radiation during the night will be reduced over a wide area. The weather conditions as the day progresses will give rise to softening of the snowpack. Towards its surface, the snowpack is moist and its surface has a crust that is not capable of bearing a load, in particular at low and intermediate altitudes. <br/> Weak layers exist in the snowpack in particular on shady slopes."
